---
const highlights = [
  {
    title: "Low-overhead telemetry collection",
    description: "Kernel-level signals collected with minimal runtime overhead."
  },
  {
    title: "Adaptive routing decisions",
    description: "Traffic redirection informed by live telemetry and health signals."
  },
  {
    title: "Runtime-aware orchestration",
    description: "Scaling and scheduling driven by real performance conditions."
  },
  {
    title: "Cluster-wide coordination",
    description: "Node-level telemetry shared to improve holistic decisions."
  }
];
---

<section id="solution" class="py-16 relative bg-zinc-900/30">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-10 items-center">
      <div class="reveal">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold font-heading tracking-tight text-white">
          Solution Overview
        </h2>
        <p class="text-slate-400 mt-5 leading-relaxed">
          KernelEye proposes a sidecar-less orchestration model that combines eBPF telemetry, adaptive traffic routing, runtime-aware scaling, and distributed node coordination to improve efficiency and responsiveness in Kubernetes environments.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        {highlights.map((item) => (
          <div class="glass-soft card-hover rounded-2xl p-6 border border-white/10 reveal">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-3">{item.title}</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">{item.description}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
